" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 524px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    12 lead ECG of atrial flutter",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 504px; height: 243px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    The 12 lead ECG of atrial flutter shows a regular rhythm with a narrow QRS complex. Flutter waves are present, best seen in leads 2, 3, and aVF (*). One flutter wave is obvious between the QRS complexes, while the second one is superimposed on the terminal portion of the QRS complex; hence there is 2:1 atrioventricular nodal block, which is the most common presentation for atrial flutter.",
